<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>
<head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="~/Areas/Binder/Content/prism.css">
    <title>jQuery</title>
    @section scripts
    {
        <script type="text/javascript" src="~/Areas/Binder/Scripts/prism.js"></script>
    }

</head>
<body>
    <div style="text-align:center">
        <img src="~/Areas/Binder/Images/jquery_logo.jpg" width="100" height="100" style="display: block; margin: auto;" />
        <h1>jQuery Data Layer</h1>
        <h5>Binder generates an jQuery data layer. Click a download link below or read the docs for a better understand of Binder's jQuery implementation</h5>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <a class="btn btn-info" href="~/api/Binder/distribution?platform=jquery" role="button">jQuery</a>
            <div class="btn-subtitle">
                Download Binder for jQuery
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
    <hr />
    <div>
        <h3>How to use Binder</h3>
        <div>
            Below is a tutorial for how to use Binder. Please follow the instructions below for binding to this web service.
        </div>

        <!--Step 1-->
        <div class="tutorial-section">
            <h4 class="tutorial-header">Step 1 - Download Files</h4>
            <div><b>Download</b> the binder files to be added to your project.</div>
        </div>

        <!--Step 2-->
        <div class="tutorial-section">
            <h4 class="tutorial-header">Step 2 - Add Files to Your Project</h4>
            <div><b>Unzip</b> the Binder package and find the unzipped folder. Drag the WebService.js file into your project.</div>
        </div>

        <!--Step 2-->
        <div class="tutorial-section">
            <h4 class="tutorial-header">Step 3 - Using the web service</h4>
            <div>Let's take a look at how to make a web service call using Binder. Below are a few examples using various input and ouput parameters.</div>
            <br/>
            <h4>No Parameters</h4>
            <pre class="language-javascript">
                <code class="language-javascript">

//Top level method
function getAllBoots() {

    //Make Binder call
    getBoots(function (response) {

    }, function (req, errorResponse) {
        alert("Error:" + errorResponse);
    })
}
            </code>
            </pre>
            

            <h4>No Body Parameters</h4>
            <pre class="language-javascript">
            <code class="language-javascript">

//Top level method
function getAllBoots() {
    //Make Binder call
    getBoots(function (response) {
    }, function (req, errorResponse) {
        alert("Error:" + errorResponse);
    })
}
            </code>
            </pre>
            
        </div>
</body>
</html>
